==English==

===Etymology===
{{nyms}}
From [[Greek]] for ''same sound''

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A word which is pronounced the same as another word but differs in spelling and meaning, for example: [[carat]], [[caret]], [[carrot]] and [[karat]].
# A letter or group of letters which are pronounced the same as another letter or group of letters.

====Related terms====
* [[homophonous]] (adjective)

====Usage notes====
An homophone is a type of [[homonym]] (a word which sounds ''or'' is spelled the same as another). An [[homograph]] is a word with the same spelling as another, but a completely unrelated meaning. Homographs are not necessarily homophones.

